# Skills Governance

## Do not create skills without permission

- **Never** add new skill files or directories (`SKILL.md`, skill folders under `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/skills-cursor/`, or similar) unless the user explicitly asks you to create or author a skill in this conversation.
- **Never** scaffold skills “for convenience,” “for next time,” or to capture workflow notes — use existing docs (`docs/handoffs/`, `docs/`, rules) instead.
- **Allowed without asking:** read and follow existing skills; edit an existing skill only when the user’s task clearly requires updating that skill’s content.
- **If a new skill seems useful:** stop and ask the user for permission. Propose name, path, and one-line purpose; wait for approval before creating anything.

## Prefer existing surfaces

| Need | Use instead of a new skill |
|------|----------------------------|
| Repeatable prompts | `docs/handoffs/*.md` |
| Always-on behavior | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` |
| One-off workflow | Reply in chat or update an existing skill |

